# Team Dynamics

## Redirects from other capitalisations

This page serves as a **redirect** from titles employing alternative capitalization schemes to their properly capitalized equivalents, adhering strictly to [Wikipedia naming conventions for capitalisation](/Wikipedia:Naming_conventions_(capitalization)). Such redirects address fundamental issues in content discovery, editorial consistency, and [internationalization](/Internationalization_and_localization) across the encyclopedia's linguistic landscape.

### Purpose and implementation
When encountering improperly capitalized article titles, editors should create redirects pointing to the **conventionally formatted** destination article. These entries:
- Facilitate natural language searching by accommodating common capitalization errors
- Resolve [cross-linguistic challenges](/Language_localisation) in title recognition
- Maintain the structural integrity of [internal linking](/Help:Link) systems

For **miscapitalized mainspace articles** (those appearing in Wikipedia's primary content area), apply the template:
&#123;&#123;[R from miscapitalisation](/Template:R_from_miscapitalisation)&#125;&#125;

This template automatically categorizes redirects requiring capitalization correction while signaling to editors that underlying links should eventually point directly to the properly capitalized target.

### Namespace considerations
The categorization protocol differs significantly across Wikipedia's namespace architecture:

1. **Mainspace redirects** (articles within Wikipedia's primary content area) exclusively warrant the &#123;&#123;[R from miscapitalisation](/Template:R_from_miscapitalisation)&#125;&#125; classification

2. **Alternative namespace occurrences** (including but not limited to [User pages](/Wikipedia:User_pages), [Talk pages](/Wikipedia:Talk_page_guidelines), and [Project namespace](/Wikipedia:Project_namespace) discussions) require:
&#123;&#123;[R from modification](/Template:R_from_modification)&#125;&#125;

This distinction preserves namespace integrity while addressing capitalization variants that don't qualify as outright errors in non-mainspace contexts.

### Editorial obligations
Editors encountering such redirects must:
- Verify the target article employs **official title capitalization**
- Update existing links pointing to the redirect so they reference the canonical article directly
- Remove redundant redirects when all inbound links have been corrected
- Consult the [Manual of Style](/Wikipedia:Manual_of_Style) for borderline capitalization cases

The system deliberately avoids automated correction to preserve editorial judgment in nuanced cases involving [proper nouns](/Proper_noun), [trademarks](/Trademark), and [cultural context](/Cultural_context) sensitivity.

## Related maintenance protocols
This redirect category intersects with several critical Wikipedia maintenance processes:
- [Wikipedia:Cleanup](/Wikipedia:Cleanup) initiatives
- [Help:Searching](/Help:Searching) optimization efforts
- [Wikipedia:Disambiguation](/Wikipedia:Disambiguation) improvements
- [Template messages](/Template_messages) standardization

Editors should cross-reference the [Wikipedia:Redirect](/Wikipedia:Redirect) guideline when addressing complex capitalization scenarios involving [acronyms](/Acronym), [initialisms](/Initialism), or [case-sensitive](/Case_sensitivity) technical terms.